Privacy Policy
The long and the short of it is: we don’t want your data. We don’t have user accounts and the only way we’ll know who you are is if you choose to contact us by e-mail or social media.
1.0 Information We Collect
We collect only crash reports and some basic usage analytics that contain no data that we can use to identify you.
1.1 Information from third parties
Apple also provide us with some crash reports and usage data, anonymised.
1.2 Information you provide to us
We do not capture any information from you when using the app, unless you chose to contact us for support or otherwise.
When you do this, the app may add some basic information about the app and your device and your recent usage of it so that we can support you. This will be visible in the message you send.
2.0 What Personal Information we collect about you and how we collect it
Good news! We collect nothing.
2.1 Third Parties we collect information from
Surprise! None at all.
3.0 What rights do you, as the data subject, have
You have all the normal rights afforded by your Country of residence.
4.0 How we store and secure the Personal Information we collect
We do not store any personal information.